firm that dissipation occurs close to regions of intense magnetic stresses,\nthus exhibiting local correlation. The distribution function-based measures\nshow a broader width compared to energy-based proxies, suggesting that energy\ntransfer is co-localized at coherent structures, but can affect the particle\ndistribution function in wider regions. The effect of interparticle collisions\non these parameters is finally discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 3 Jan 2021 22:41:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 26 Jun 2021 15:00:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-30"}
